Probability(Purchased an order/Planned to purchase) is equal to 0.8000

In [12]:

p3 = cumpoisson[1] #Probability of selling 1 or more cars
p4 = p2-p3 
print('Probability that in a given week he will sell 2 or more but less than 5 cars is %1.4f'%p4)

Probability that in a given week he will sell 2 or more but less than 5 cars is 0.6161

Q5. One of the real life industry scenario where we can use the concepts learned in Applied statistics is Aerospace/Aerostructure industry.I chose this as i am working as a stress engineer for aerostructures industry.The main aim of the work is to conduct Static, Fatigue and DT analysis on the aircraft and certify them.

  1. Using the concepts learned in applied statistics we can calculate the life of aircraft components much more efficiently.
  2. With the huge amount of data available, we can deploy various methods of statistical analysis and predict the probability of failure of the structure and thereby improve reliability.
  3. We can also analyse the various trends in the past data and find out which of the components face higher risks of failure and improve upon them.

With the increase in the amount of data everywhere the methods of statistics find application in all areas.

A few suggestions:

  1. Quality of data - The quality of data could have been a little more better like the column such as Team Launch contains multiple year data like an interval of years.

  2. Quantity of data - There are around 61 teams information that has been provided.The more the amount of data the more accurate inferences we can make out.

  3. Velocity of data - We can gather more information quickly and efficiently if we keep recording the information after every matches.

  4. Variety of data - The variety help us distinguish between various datapoints more efficiently and this can be done by improving the amount of information given by the dataset.

The final conclusion is that the Company X can approach any of the first 5 teams which has played more games,has more wins and experience.

In [62]:
Ho = "The funds raised by the companies that are operating and closed down do no differ significantly"   
Ha = "The funds raised by the companies that are operating and closed down differ significantly"   

x = np.array(df4[(df4['OperatingState'] == 'Closed')].Funds_in_million)  
y = np.array(df4[(df4['OperatingState'] == 'Operating')].Funds_in_million) 

t, p_value  = stats.ttest_ind(x,y, axis = 0)  #Two sample t_test
if p_value < 0.05: # Setting our significance level at 5%
    print(f'{Ha} as the p_value ({p_value}) < 0.05')
else:
    print(f'{Ho} as the p_value ({p_value}) > 0.05')

The funds raised by the companies that are operating and closed down do no differ significantly as the p_value (0.1931747168826862) > 0.05
